    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-06T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-06T06:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/557: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece (<persName type="from">Morris</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-06T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 6, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 6—8:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. Your 48.<note n="19" xml:id="d283fn19">Not printed.</note> I made
                    representations on October 1st. Foreign <pb facs="0490" n="400" xml:id="pg_400"
                    /> Office informs me verbally that <persName corresp="#p_VE1"
                        >Venizelos</persName> is personally drafting a reply which I may expect to
                    receive within a few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
